HEADWORD: Pedipalpus
<hw>Ped`i*pal"pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pedipalpi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See <er>Pes</er>, and
<er>Palpus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the second pair
of mouth organs of arachnids. In some they are leglike, but in others,
as the scorpion, they terminate in a claw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

